wordBank.name: Class Diagram
wordBank.description: Describes the structure (but not the behavior) of an OOP solution.

wordBank.name: Object Diagram
wordBank.description: Diagram to model different object structures that can result from a design

wordBank.name: Sequence Diagram
wordBank.description: Diagram that captures interactions between multiple objects for a given scenario.

wordBank.name: Integration Testing
wordBank.description: Testing whether different parts of the software work together.

wordBank.name: Unit Testing
wordBank.description: Testing each unit of software works as designed.

wordBank.name: Alpha Testing
wordBank.description: Testing by users, under controlled conditions.

wordBank.name: Beta Testing
wordBank.description: Testing by subset of target users, in natural work setting.

wordBank.name: Dependency Injection
wordBank.description: Injecting' objects to replace current dependencies with different object.

wordBank.name: Test Coverage
wordBank.description: Metric used to measure the extent to which testing exercises the code.

wordBank.name: Coupling
wordBank.description: A measure of the degree of dependence.

wordBank.name: Cohesion
wordBank.description: Measure of how strongly-related and focused the various responsibilities of a component are.
